HEADWORD: Oreoselin
<hw>O`re*os"e*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white crystalline substance which is obtained indirectly from the
root of an umbelliferous plant (<spn>Imperatoria Oreoselinum</spn>), and
yields resorcin on decomposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oreosoma</ent>⟦br⟧
